    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-column, narrative-driven structure is used to guide the user through a learning journey. It starts by deconstructing common PK/PD misconceptions (Vd, albumin), transitions to the core message of holistic patient care ("wood for the trees"), presents a real-world failure case study to ground the theory in practice, and concludes with the expert's cyclical approach to TDM. This linear flow is optimal for educational content, building complexity progressively. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Case Study Data -> Goal: Change -> Viz/Method: Line Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) showing VCM concentration over time. -> Justification: A line chart is the most effective way to visualize the dramatic and dangerous spike in drug concentration detailed in the case study, making the data instantly understandable. NO SVG/Mermaid. | TDM Cycle -> Goal: Organize -> Viz/Method: Flowchart created with structured HTML/CSS (Tailwind) -> Justification: Clearly illustrates the iterative, cyclical nature of the expert TDM process without using prohibited libraries. NO SVG/Mermaid. | PK Misconceptions -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Method: Two-column layout with Unicode icons -> Justification: Provides a clear, side-by-side comparison of misconceptions versus reality. NO SVG/Mermaid. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
